Sacking means something quite different for NFL coaches on the first day following the end of the regular season.

Five coaches have already been fired today in a tradition known as Black Monday, as teams not progressing to the playoffs try to get a head start on next year.

As of noon today, the head coaches of the the Detroit Lions, Tampa Bay Buccaneers, Washington Redskins, Minnesota Vikings, and Cleveland Browns have all been let go.

If any more firings are announced today, it may be one of the worst Black Mondays in recent history. Last year was noted as being an especially brutal year with six firings.

