The dismissals started early this year, with news that the Cleveland Browns would not be keeping coach Rob Chudzinski being released late last night.

As Monday morning dawned, two other coaches expected to be fired joined Chudzinksi on the unemployment line.

The Minnesota Vikings fired head coach Leslie Frazier and the Washington Redskins fired head coach and Executive Vice President Mike Shanahan in announcements made before 10am.

Shanahan was among those expected to be out of the job for the way he dealt with quarterback Robert Griffin III's ACL injury last season.

Griffin injured his right knee in a game against the Baltimore Ravens on December 9, 2012.  

