Instead of letting Griffin recover from the injury, Shanahan put him back on the field after missing just one game. On January 6, the Redskins went up against the Seattle Seahawks in an NFL wildcard game and Griffin aggravated the injury, having to undergo surgery three days later.

Griffin was back playing this season but the leg injury seems to have slowed him down noticeably.

By lunchtime, two other coaches had been fired: Greg Schiano of the Tampa Bay Buccaneers and Jim Schwartz of the Detroit Lions.  

